<subSubSection id="6D837C85103BFFA4DBE2FC084D8B2888" pageId="30" pageNumber="131" type="discussion">
<paragraph id="25262F0E103BFFA4DBE2FC084D8B2888" blockId="30.[151,1437,151,933]" pageId="30" pageNumber="131">
<emphasis id="17EDF31C103BFFA4DBE2FC084D012870" bold="true" box="[199,308,835,861]" pageId="30" pageNumber="131">Remarks</emphasis>
. 
<taxonomicName id="E299548D103BFFA4DA63FC084DF82870" authorityName="Okajima &amp; Masumoto" authorityYear="2022" box="[326,461,835,861]" class="Insecta" family="Phlaeothripidae" genus="Asianthrips" kingdom="Animalia" order="Thysanoptera" pageId="30" pageNumber="131" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="sufflavus">
<emphasis id="17EDF31C103BFFA4DA63FC084DF82870" box="[326,461,835,861]" italics="true" pageId="30" pageNumber="131">A. sufflavus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is very similar to 
<taxonomicName id="E299548D103BFFA4D98FFC084F2B2870" authorityName="Okajima &amp; Masumoto" authorityYear="2022" box="[682,798,835,861]" class="Insecta" family="Phlaeothripidae" genus="Asianthrips" kingdom="Animalia" order="Thysanoptera" pageId="30" pageNumber="131" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="pallens">
<emphasis id="17EDF31C103BFFA4D98FFC084F2B2870" box="[682,798,835,861]" italics="true" pageId="30" pageNumber="131">A. pallens</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
from 
<collectingCountry id="5D8E6F9E103BFFA4D84CFC084F8B2870" box="[873,958,835,861]" name="Taiwan" pageId="30" pageNumber="131">Taiwan</collectingCountry>
, and the difference between these two is discussed under 
<taxonomicName id="E299548D103BFFA4DA71FC2C4DF328AC" authorityName="Okajima &amp; Masumoto" authorityYear="2022" box="[340,454,871,897]" class="Insecta" family="Phlaeothripidae" genus="Asianthrips" kingdom="Animalia" order="Thysanoptera" pageId="30" pageNumber="131" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="pallens">
<emphasis id="17EDF31C103BFFA4DA71FC2C4DF328AC" box="[340,454,871,897]" italics="true" pageId="30" pageNumber="131">A. pallens</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
. The chaetotaxy of the dorsum of the distal antennal segments of this species may be peculiar among the genus.
</paragraph>
